ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me comp
ile my findings.\n\nKey observations:\n\n1. **Full Chain Integrity**: The infras
tructure bootstrap PR includes DB (migrations, entities), API (modules for auth,
blocks, reports, content moderation, admin, health), Mobile (main.dart with Sent
ry, local package dependencies), Admin (login, dashboard), Shared types (OpenAPI
generated), Design system (Widgetbook + components), BDD tests, CI pipeline. Thi
s looks quite complete for an infrastructure bootstrap.\n\n2. **Specification Co
mpliance**:\n   - NestJS: Modules seem reasonably well-structured. However:\n   
 - `RegisterDto` lacks validation decorators (only has plain fields, no `@IsStri
ng()`, `@IsNotEmpty()`, etc.) even though `class-validator` is installed and `Va
lidationPipe` is configured globally.\n     - The `AuthController` uses `"api/v1
/auth"` as path, but `main.ts` also sets global prefix `"api/v1"`. This means th
e actual path would be `/api/v1/api/v1/auth` - a **major bug**.\n     - Actually
wait, let me re-check. `main.ts` line 21: `app.setGlobalPrefix("api/v1");`. `Aut
hController` line 5: `@Controller("api/v1/auth")`. So the full path would indeed
be `/api/v1/api/v1/auth`. That\'s wrong.\n     - The OpenAPI auth.yaml defines `
/api/v1/auth/login`, but the controller\'s path would be `/api/v1/api/v1/auth/lo
gin`.\n   - Flutter: The mobile `main.dart` uses Sentry. Widgetbook is set up. B
LoC is not yet used since this is infrastructure.\n   - DB naming: The migration
uses snake_case for tables and columns, which is good. `char(36)` for UUIDs, `da
tetime(3)` for timestamps. Soft delete `deleted_at` is present. This looks compl
iant with the design doc expectations.\n\n3. **Contract Consistency**:\n   - The
OpenAPI `auth.yaml` defines `LoginRequest`, `RefreshTokenRequest`, `LoginRespons
e`.\n   - But the generated TS/Dart models only cover login and refresh. The `au
th.yaml` does NOT define the `register` endpoint that exists in `AuthController`
. The controller has `POST register` with `phone` and `birth_date`, but the YAML
only has `login` and `refresh`.\n   - Also the `RegisterDto` in the API doesn\'t
match any OpenAPI schema.\n   - `shared-types/src/index.ts` exports from generat
ed auth, but the API `AuthService` uses its own hardcoded types/stub responses i
